Collophore. Anterior side with 18–20 chaetae, 9 proximal spine-like chaetae, 1 thin and 1–2 normal ciliated chaetae, 5–6 ciliated chaetae apically acuminate and 2 mac distally; posterior side with 18–19 chaetae (2 unpaired), 8 spines, 9–10 thin ciliated chaetae widely distributed and 1 smooth chaeta distally; lateral flap with about 67 chaetae, 10 smooth and 57 ciliated (
Fig. 76E
).
